%N A397566 a(0) = 0; for n >= 1, a(n) is the smallest number whose Hamming distance from a(n-1) is n^2.
%e A397566 a(1) = 1 = 1_2. The smallest number at Hamming distance 2^2 = 4 from 1 flips its single 1-bit and the three lowest 0-bits, giving 1110_2 = 14 = a(2).
%o A397566 (Python)
%o A397566 a=0
%o A397566 for n in range(1,13):
%o A397566    a ^= (1 << n*n) - 1
%o A397566    print(a)
